<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-126-278 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 897 346</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  June 20 1991 v17 n13 p31(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Object-oriented market to reach $3.6B. (billion)andM;</TITLE><SUMMARY>The Object Technology Sourcebook published by Ovum Ltd and theObject Management Group maintains that US revenues fromobject-oriented systems will reach $3.664 billion in 1996, up from$559 million in 1991.andP;  In addition to listing 150 currentobject-oriented products, the report also offers the applicationsfor which they are being used.andP;  The report claims that many largecorporations already have internal development projects centeringon object-oriented technology.andP;  The four main product areas listedin the report are data bases, languages, computer-aided softwareengineering and program development software tools.andP;  The fastinggrowing area is application developer toolkits which is expectedto grow at 80 percent each year and reach $474 million in 1996.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ovum Ltd. (Reports).andO;Topic:     Market ShareAnalysisObject-oriented data basesReportsFuture of ComputingObject-oriented languagesObject Management GroupComputer-aided software engineeringObject-oriented programming.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Total revenues from object-oriented systems. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>LONDON, England -- The first real systems based on object-oriented technologyare now in commercial use.andP;  And their users are beginning to reap thebenefits, according to the Object Technology Sourcebook recently published byOvum Ltd. in collaboration with the Object Management Group.andM;Ovum estimates that total revenues from object-oriented systems will growfrom $559 million (U.S.) in 1991 to $3.664 billion (U.S.) in 1996.andP;  Thereport gives details of more than 150 current products and their suppliers,and describes the applications for which they are being used.andM;Objects are a natural way to model the real world, says Ovum.andP;  That is whyobject technology is being used to model complex systems by manufacturingcompanies and by users in the telecommunications, military and defencesectors.andM;Most large corporations now have substantial internal development programsfor object technology.andP;  One reasor for this is the maintainability ofobject-oriented systems.andP;  &quot;Because change is limited to one area of thesystem, its impact is reduced,&quot; says Judith Jeffcoate, lead author.andP;  &quot;Objecttechnology can thus reduce the cost of maintenance.&quot;andM;The report identifies four main product areas: languages, databases,application development tools and computer-aided software engineering (CASE)tools.andP;  A wide range of object-oriented languages and tools are alreadyavailable, though C++ remains the language of choice.andP;  The fastest growingsector -- application developers' toolkits -- is set to grow by an average of80 per cent per year over the next five years, to be worth $474 million by1996.andM;In another report, Databases for Objects: The Market Opportunity, Ovum examsobject-oriented databases.andP;  Most relational database vendors are extendingtheir products to support objects, says Ovum.andP;  Building on an existing userbase, it is these extended relational databases which will dominate themarket during the early 1990s.andM;The report identifies two vertical markets where databases for objects willplay a key role: engineering and multimedia.andM;According to the report, relational database vendors are reacting quickly.andO;Some already support binary large objects or 'blobs.'andP;  Others are addingobject-oriented features to their fourth generation languages.andP;  Ovum expectsthese extended relational databases to account for 52 per cent of the totalDBMS market in 1995 with revenues of $4.2 billion (U.S.) in the U.S.andP;  andEurope.andM;The Object Technology Sourcebook is available at a price of $495 (U.S.) andDatabases for Objects: the Market Opportunity is available for $1,200 (U.S.).andO;Ovum can be reached at 071 255 2670.andO;</TEXT></DOC>